    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix memory leak in MMSE processing functions\n\n### Summary\nThe MMSE processing functions in the LTE UE transport layer had several memory allocation points without proper error handling. When malloc failed during MMSE processing, the functions would either crash or leak memory, causing instability in the UE PHY layer.\n\nThe issue was particularly evident when running the UE in high-load scenarios where malloc might fail due to memory pressure. This would cause the functions to return without freeing previously allocated memory blocks.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_UE_TRANSPORT/dlsch_demodulation.c`: Added proper NULL checks after malloc calls and cleanup code for error cases in:\n  - `mmse_processing_core`\n  - `mmse_processing_core_flp` \n  - `mult_mmse_rxdataF`\n  - `mult_mmse_chan_est`\n\nThe changes ensure that if any malloc fails, all previously allocated memory is properly freed before returning from the function, preventing memory leaks.\n"
}